      <div id ="main-2">
  <p>Scorching Sea (PC, March 2015)</p>
  <p>Language: Javascript, CSS</p>
  <p>Team Size: 4</p>
  <p>Roles: Game designer, programmer, and artist</p>
  <p>An isometric, real-time, Oregon Trail-like game set in the post apocalyptic future where water is a scarcity. Since our team did not use any engines, I made the engine from scratch. I programmed the transformation of the world in order to give the game an isometric view and I programmed the collision detection, and resource management so the game can be efficient. I also made the art direction and some sprites.</p>
  <a href="http://people.ucsc.edu/~brlgomez/20/Scorching_Sea/scorching_sea.html">Play</a>
